post_text: Last week, the State Board of Education announced that the department of education would waive up to a maximum of 3 school days for schools to plan re-opening activities, preparation, and training on new protocols and processes to be implemented during the COVID-19 pandemic. This means that the first day of school for all Jumoke Academy scholars is now on Thursday, September 3, 2020. We believe these extra days given to our staff members to train, learn, and prepare our environment, will make Jumoke Academy an even safer educational environment for our scholars.

post_text: Congrats to 4th grade teacher Mrs. Mercedes! Also, we would like to thank Connecticut Trial Firm, LLC for holding such a great contest!
shared_text:
Connecticut Trial Firm, LLC is at Jumoke Academy.
August 29, 2019 at 7:18 AM · Hartford, CT ·

We are thrilled to announce Yesenia Mercedes from Jumoke Academy in Hartford as our 2019 Tremendous Teacher!

Mrs. Mercedes teaches 4th Grade. She was born in Hartford and served our country in Iraq. She mentors students, serves on committees, and is loved by the Jumoke Academy community.

We donated a $400 Staples Gift Card and a box of supplies to help her 4th grade class!!!

#values #community #teacher #veterans

WWW.NECHARTERS.ORG
Northeast Charter Schools Network | Supporting and expanding New York's and Connecticut's quality public charter school movement

Connecticut Charter Schools Association
March 15, 2019 at 10:14 AM ·

Connecticut has 23 Public Charter Schools. These schools serve over 10,400 students from 83 communities. 88% are students of color and nearly 65% are low income. This is a glimpse inside six of those schools. Odyssey Community School ISAAC - Interdistrict School for Arts and Communication Booker T. Washington Academy, Inc. Highville Charter School Jumoke Academy Common Ground High School, Urban Farm, and Environmental Education Center

post_text: Raffle tickets for our Heritage Gala "Destination Raffle" are now available! You can purchase them online at bidpal.net/heritagegala OR in person at our Central Office from today on, or in our school buildings starting Monday! Tickets are $10 and the winner will get his or her choice between 3 destinations! All proceeds go towards our mission to educate the children of the Greater Hartford area!

shared_text:
Connecticut Charter Schools Association
September 10, 2018 at 10:58 AM ·

Jumoke, a Nigerian tribal word for "the child is loved", is the guiding principle for educating students at Jumoke Academy. Principal Dr. Finley works to ensure this vision comes to life each and every day.

Share if you believe every child deserves a great school that helps them achieve their dreams!
